.Volumes {\n\t\tif v.Name == caVolumeName {\n\t\t\thasVolume = true\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif !hasVolume {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"deployment manifest missing required volume %q\", caVolumeName)\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n### Change 4: Call `validateDeploymentManifest` in `getDeploymentObject`\n\nInsert the validation call after `r.updateVolumes()` and before the `return deployment, nil` at the end of `getDeploymentObject`.\n\n**Old (lines 98-101):**\n```go\n\tif err := r.updateVolumes(deployment, istiocsr, resourceLabels); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update volume %s/%s: %w\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName(), err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn deployment, nil\n```\n\n**New:**\n```go\n\tif err := r.updateVolumes(deployment, istiocsr, resourceLabels); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update volume %s/%s: %w\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName(), err)\n\t}\n\n\tif err := validateDeploymentManifest(deployment); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, common.NewIrrecoverableError(err, \"invalid istio-csr deployment manifest\")\n\t}\n\n\treturn deployment, nil\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments_test.go`\n\nAdd this test function at the end of the file (before the closing of the file):\n\n```go\nfunc TestValidateDeploymentManifest(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname       string\n\t\tdeployment *appsv1.Deployment\n\t\twantErr    string\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"valid deployment with required container and volume\",\n\t\t\tdeployment: &appsv1.Deployment{\n\t\t\t\tSpec: appsv1.DeploymentSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\tTemplate: corev1.PodTemplateSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSpec: corev1.PodSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tContainers: []corev1.Container{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Name: istiocsrContainerName},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tVolumes: []corev1.Volume{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Name: caVolumeName},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: \"\",\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"missing required container\",\n\t\t\tdeployment: &appsv1.Deployment{\n\t\t\t\tSpec: appsv1.DeploymentSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\tTemplate: corev1.PodTemplateSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSpec: corev1.PodSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tContainers: []corev1.Container{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Name: \"wrong-container\"},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tVolumes: []corev1.Volume{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Name: caVolumeName},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: fmt.Sprintf(\"deployment manifest missing required container %q\", istiocsrContainerName),\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"missing required volume\",\n\t\t\tdeployment: &appsv1.Deployment{\n\t\t\t\tSpec: appsv1.DeploymentSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\tTemplate: corev1.PodTemplateSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSpec: corev1.PodSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tContainers: []corev1.Container{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Name: istiocsrContainerName},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tVolumes: []corev1.Volume{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{Name: \"wrong-volume\"},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: fmt.Sprintf(\"deployment manifest missing required volume %q\", caVolumeName),\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"empty containers and no volumes\",\n\t\t\tdeployment: &appsv1.Deployment{\n\t\t\t\tSpec: appsv1.DeploymentSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\tTemplate: corev1.PodTemplateSpec{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSpec: corev1.PodSpec{},\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: fmt.Sprintf(\"deployment manifest missing required container %q\", istiocsrContainerName),\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\terr := validateDeploymentManifest(tt.deployment)\n\t\t\tif tt.wantErr == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"validateDeploymentManifest() unexpected error: %v\", err)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\t\tt.Fatalf(\"validateDeploymentManifest() expected error %q, got nil\", tt.wantErr)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif err.Error() != tt.wantErr {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"validateDeploymentManifest() error = %q, want %q\", err.Error(), tt.wantErr)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of all changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go` | Promote `caVolumeName` const to package level; remove local redefinition in `updateVolumeWithIssuerCA`; add `validateDeploymentManifest` function; call it in `getDeploymentObject` after `r.updateVolumes()` |\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments_test.go` | Add `TestValidateDeploymentManifest` table-driven test with 4 cases |\n\n## Commands to run\n\n```bash\ncd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/cert-manager-operator-treatment\n\n# Verify it compiles\ngo build ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/...\n\n# Run the new test\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/ -run TestValidateDeploymentManifest -v\n\n# Run all istiocsr tests to check for regressions\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/...\n```\n\n## Design notes\n\n- The `caVolumeName` constant is promoted from a local const inside `updateVolumeWithIssuerCA` to a package-level const so both the validation function and the volume setup code reference the same value.\n- The validation call is placed after `r.updateVolumes()` because the `root-ca` volume is added dynamically (not present in the bindata YAML). This means the guard validates the fully-assembled deployment before it's returned to `createOrApplyDeployments` for cluster application — catching both bindata corruption (wrong container name) and volume setup failures (edge cases where `updateVolumeWithIssuerCA` isn't called).\n- The function mirrors the trustmanager's `validateDeploymentManifest` exactly in structure: loop to find container by name, loop to find volume by name, return descriptive error on missing.\n- The 4th test case (\"empty containers and no volumes\") confirms the container check short-circuits before the volume check when both are missing."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tok